      "body": "* Pull [`REFS.JSON`](https://github.com/Niema-Lab/Reference-Genomes/releases/latest/download/REFS.json) from the internet again\r\n    * I did this previously, but I reverted to a hard-coded `REFS_JSON` variable for speed when failing to download (e.g. no internet)\r\n    * Now, I first check if the reference genome exists locally if given a GenBank ID or file path\r\n    * Thus, I only attempt to download `REFS.JSON` if I determine I absolutely need to download a reference genome\r\n    * Also, I only attempt to download `REFS.JSON` once, and if it fails, I remember (and also fail immediately everywhere it's attempted)"
